[[File:Normansfield Theatre - geograph.org.uk - 49803.jpg|thumb|Normansfield Theatre exterior]] [[File:Normansfield Theatre Stage - geograph.org.uk - 49802.jpg|thumb|Stage of the theatre]] The '''Normansfield Theatre '''is a [[Victorian era]] building located in [[Teddington]], England.
The theatre is on the site of [[Normansfield Hospital]], which was a self-sufficient Victorian hospital complex run by Dr [[John Langdon Down]]. The hospital was where Doctor Langdon Down conducted the pioneering research into the syndrome now known as [[Down's Syndrome]]. The theatre was constructed in 1877 and completed in 1879 for the use of the patients.<ref name=lost>{{cite web | url=http://ezitis.myzen.co.uk/normansfield.html | title=Normansfield Hospital | work=Lost Hospitals of London | accessdate=5 May 2014}}</ref>
The theatre is held in care by the Langdon Down Centre Trust.<ref name="Arts">{{cite web | url=http://www.artsrichmond.org.uk/society-detail.php?id=15 | title=Langdon Down Centre Trust | publisher=Arts Richmond | work=Directory of societies and affiliates | accessdate=15 November 2013}}</ref>
Work on restoring the previously derelict [[Grade II* listed]]<ref name="LIsting">{{NHLE | num=1065379 | desc=Normansfield Hospital |accessdate=15 November 2013}}</ref> building began in 2010.<ref name="Ambrose">{{cite news | url= http://www.yourlocalguardian.co.uk/news/local/richmondnews/10763973.Former_Teddington_hospital_removed_from__at_risk__register/ | title=Former Normansfield Hospital removed from 'at risk' register | work=[[Richmond and Twickenham Times]] | date=28 October 2013 | accessdate=15 November 2013 | author=Ambrose, Tom}}</ref> It has now been converted for residential use and the former hospital workshops have been re-developed as social housing. The building has been removed from English Heritage’s At Risk register.<ref name="Ambrose"/>
It is a popular filming location, such as for ''[[Agatha Christie's Poirot]]'' in the episode "[[The Tragedy at Marsdon Manor]]", "[[The Case of the Missing Will]]", "[[Poirot's Early Cases#Double Sin|Double Sin]]" (1990),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymotion.com/video/xpt2tv_s5e4-agatha-christie-s-poirot-the-case-of-the-missing-will_fun|title=Agatha Christie's Poirot - The Case of the Missing Will|publisher=Daily Motion}}</ref> "[[After the Funeral#Television|After the funeral]] (2005)" the 2009 film ''[[Dorian Gray (2009 film)|Dorian Gray]]'' and the [[ITV Network|ITV]] series ''[[Downton Abbey]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://teddingtontown.co.uk/2010/11/08/video-update-2/ |title=Video Update &#124; Teddington, Middlesex, UK |publisher= Teddingtontown.co.uk |date=8 November 2010 |accessdate=15 November 2013}}</ref>
